---
description: humanize prose, remove ai slop, and rewrite copy in files without changing code behavior
globs:
  - "**/*.{md,mdx,txt,html,tsx,jsx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

When asked to humanize text, reduce AI slop, or make prose sound less robotic:

1. Read the full target text or enough file context to understand purpose and audience.
2. Diagnose generic, padded, repetitive, or under-specified prose.
3. Rewrite in balanced mode:
   - preserve meaning
   - improve clarity and specificity
   - remove filler
   - smooth repetitive cadence
   - avoid fake personality, fake typos, or invented details
4. Edit prose only. Do not change code behavior, identifiers, placeholders, or formatting unless asked.
5. After editing, return a short summary with:
   - changes made
   - why
   - notes (only if needed)

Default priorities:
clarity -> specificity -> natural rhythm -> concision
